Code Requirements
Python 3.6+
Opencv(pip install opencv-contrib-python)
Tkinter(Available in python)
PIL (pip install Pillow)
Pandas(pip install pandas)
Numpy(pip install numpy)

--Notes--
It will require high processing power(I have 8 GB RAM & 1 GB Nvidia GT740M Graphic Card)
Noisy image can reduce your accuracy so quality of images matter.
Make sure opencv-python is uninstalled as both  opencv-contrib-python and opencv-python cause conflict.
You can download the haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml by cloning or from https://github.com/opencv/opencv/tree/master/data/haarcascades.
you need to download Trainner.yml file from:https://github.com/codingforentrepreneurs/OpenCV-Python-Series/blob/master/src/recognizers/face-trainner.yml
